Figure 6f, g displays the Raman spectra and their quantified analyses on LiTFSI dissociation. In general, there are three TFSI− forms, including free TFSI−, contact ion pairs (CIP), and aggregated ion pairs (AGG), corresponding to the Raman bands at 740.9, 744.2, and 748.7 cm−1, respectively [63, 66]. Among them, the free TFSI− represents the LiTFSI dissociation degree, which undergoes an enormous increase from 49% to 64% after introducing In-MOF nanorods, thereby showing a considerable contribution to improving σ. Furthermore, Lewis acid–base interactions between In-MOF and the Li salt immobilize the TFSI− anions, resulting in improved \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
